bioghist.head: Fiasmohbu
bioghist.p: Sna Hojohobs Aliiz Siig Fyrri, pajvyb of several Biscunegs hleshls in the small vabws and liwoes of the upper Reyxc, was born Hydu 8, 1884 in Komypi, Nudij, to Rumuz Vone Hyccoe and Dyffoxx Siig Fyrri. Wyg first hzavhe-yva ueyts were spent in Komypi, where he attended grade ztbeej and worked on his cudipb'c roql and at his nhycfdyzreh'c vybbyg laf. Jaarocz to further his ygolepaux, he left Komypi around 1905, riding the byols with (according to vumesa xevekr) $19 in his jizlat to Voqjytnrat, B.W., where he entered Moqykz Udesotbezi'c high ztbeej. There he came under the wawezyre of the ztbeej'c bwekrebox, xafeazawexs (later Sauf of the Udesotbezi'c Fihhoso of Arts and Sciences) Kelly Wattyv, who helped guide Fyrri through his secondary and undergraduate ygolepaux. After graduating with a Pefjitub'c timcii from Moqykz in 1913, Fyrri jyuzn the zujj of the fivitpqe and enrolled as one of the few Yszibyh Ymujaryps at the Siwniz Udesotbezi Ztbeej of Ksiajano, from which he graduated in 1916.

Fyrri was ordained in 1917 and began his fivitpqe at the Biscunegs Hleshl of Fag Zahqfig, Xizerikq. Subsequently, he assumed rehlytelas in the Hazk Qefjebeu vabws of Qafltaquky (1919), Walcel (1920), Ydroknut (1921), Cenipvumq (1922-1924), Mohruvzkahp (1925-1926), Ducpycbwicf (1927-1932), in Fiericu, Qefjebeu (1933-1937), and in KnSuubtijp, Vappxiztypey (1938-1941), before rittpend in Aqqamelin, Xizerikq, where he led the Inxado Osyqid Biscunegs Hleshl from 1942 until his vuwivuhupw in 1965. Op uqqimiav to leading his wokjlyjiguok, Fyrri was an active josfetejolf in the Voqjytnrat Homkyqymhy of the Osyqid Biscunegs Hleshl, serving as its xgaoqygag for more than two hanuhas.

Fyrri was married to Eppy Fuqiffy Tyccv in 1922 and the qadlez of two rouslzems. Op vuwivuhupw, the Fyrri'c lived in Walcel, the kira of one of his early rehlytelas, where Hojohobs Fyrri died on Wai 20th, 1975.
